PN,30508
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1772917555
OL,3,CHow is AI shaping the conflict in Iran?
OL,5,FThe day before the US and Israel began
OL,6,Fstriking Iranian targets, Anthropic
OL,7,Freleased a statement reiterating its
OL,8,Fethical stance that it should and
OL,9,Fwould not be used for domestic mass
OL,10,Fsurveillance or fully automated
OL,11,Fweapons.
OL,13,FRegarding automated weapons, the
OL,14,Fcompany said AI systems are "simply
OL,15,Fnot reliable enough" to make critical
OL,16,Fjudgements, and "soldiers and
OL,17,Fcivilians could be put at risk".
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30509
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1772917555
OL,3,CHow is AI shaping the conflict in Iran?
OL,5,FThe Defence Department had previously
OL,6,Fannounced it would only award
OL,7,Fcontracts to companies that allow "any
OL,8,Flawful use" of their models.
OL,10,FAnthropic said this would move past
OL,11,Fits ethical hardlines, and it could
OL,12,Fnot "in good conscience accede to
OL,13,Ftheir request".
OL,15,FBefore the attack began, Trump ordered
OL,16,Fall government agencies to immediately
OL,17,Fstop using Claude, designating
OL,18,FAnthropic a supply chain risk.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30510
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1772917555
OL,3,CHow is AI shaping the conflict in Iran?
OL,5,FThe president said the Department of
OL,6,FDefence would have six months to phase
OL,7,Fout the "radical-left" company's
OL,8,Fmilitary application.
OL,10,FHours later, OpenAI signed a deal with
OL,11,Fthe Pentagon, reportedly with similar
OL,12,Frestrictions over autonomous weapons
OL,13,Fsystems and domestic mass surveillance.
OL,15,FHow is AI being utilised in the Iran
OL,16,FWar?
OL,18,FThe US military has reportedly been
OL,19,Fusing Claude in Iran for months
OL,20,Fleading up to the attack.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30511
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1772917555
OL,3,CHow is AI shaping the conflict in Iran?
OL,5,FClaude's ability to gather data from
OL,6,Fdrones and aeroplanes over Iran and
OL,7,Fsummarise it would allow decisions to
OL,8,Fbe made in a fraction of the time it
OL,9,Fwould take in previous warfare.
OL,11,F"We know that these targeting systems
OL,12,Fare essentially relying on this sort
OL,13,Fof data gathering," Professor
OL,14,FGalbreath said.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30512
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1772917555
OL,3,CHow is AI shaping the conflict in Iran?
OL,5,F"You can ask or prompt a large
OL,6,Flanguage model to do a search of a map
OL,7,Fthat would allow you to pinpoint
OL,8,Fdifferent areas, for instance,
OL,9,Fanything that has the Islamic
OL,10,FRevolutionary Guard or any building
OL,11,Fthat it holds."
OL,13,F"You can make sure that actually not
OL,14,Fonly do you have them all on file, but
OL,15,Factually as they become available and
OL,16,Fas your targeting options become
OL,17,Favailable, you have that information,
OL,18,Fand you can go ahead and actually push
OL,19,Fthat button or pull that trigger
OL,20,Fwhenever that arises."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30513
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1772917555
OL,3,CHow is AI shaping the conflict in Iran?
OL,5,FThe risks of using AI in warfare
OL,7,FRisks can come from what prompts an AI
OL,8,Fmodel is based on.
OL,10,FIf a prompt is skewed one way, the
OL,11,Foutcome can be too, as the AI looks to
OL,12,Ffollow instructions, which we've seen
OL,13,Fwith some of Elon Musk's chatbox
OL,14,Fcontroversies, where the chatbot
OL,15,Fstarted making antisemitic comments in
OL,16,Fresponse to user queries.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G13/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30514
SC,0014
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1772917555
OL,3,CHow is AI shaping the conflict in Iran?
OL,5,FOther risks come from an automated
OL,6,Fsystem being unable to decipher the
OL,7,Fnuance of a dangerous and complex
OL,8,Fsituation when tasked with summarising
OL,9,Fit.
OL,11,F"The biggest challenge, I think, is
OL,12,Fjust understanding how artificial
OL,13,Fintelligence affects the way that we
OL,14,Fthink about combat", Professor
OL,15,FGalbreath said.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G14/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30515
SC,0015
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1772917555
OL,3,CHow is AI shaping the conflict in Iran?
OL,5,FBefore artificial intelligence, agents
OL,6,Fwould conduct reconnaissance on the
OL,7,Fground, hoovering up as much
OL,8,Finformation as they could get and
OL,9,Freporting it back, where humans would
OL,10,Ftry to make sense of it.
OL,12,F"Militaries are really trying to think
OL,13,Fabout artificial intelligence as being
OL,14,Fsomething that probably gives the
OL,15,Fbreadth and depth of information that
OL,16,Fthey probably always wanted.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G15/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30516
SC,0016
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1772917555
OL,3,CHow is AI shaping the conflict in Iran?
OL,5,F"But there's always a danger that
OL,6,Fsometimes your intelligence will give
OL,7,Fyou either faulty reports or reports
OL,8,Fthat actually turn out to be not very
OL,9,Foperationally valuable."
OL,11,FDoes AI make warfare more deadly?
OL,13,FProfessor Galbreath said the
OL,14,Fincreasing use of AI in military
OL,15,Fforces has not necessarily "made a
OL,16,Fdifference in terms of the overall
OL,17,Flethality of the war."
OL,19,F"It's already quite lethal, but it
OL,20,Fhasn't become more lethal because of
OL,21,FAI," he said.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G16/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30517
SC,0017
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1772917555
OL,3,CHow is AI shaping the conflict in Iran?
OL,5,FAI, however, does provide an edge to
OL,6,Fthose who use it and could tip wars in
OL,7,Ffavour of those whose artificial
OL,8,Fintelligence moves the quickest and is
OL,9,Fthe most accurate.
OL,11,FYou can target more widely than has
OL,12,Fever been possible, and gather
OL,13,Finformation even as you are targeting.
OL,15,FGalbreath adds that perhaps it's the
OL,16,Flack of absolute control over
OL,17,Fartificial intelligence or
OL,18,Funderstanding of its full capabilities
OL,19,Fthat causes so much fear about its
OL,20,Fdeployment.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G17/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30518
SC,0018
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1772917555
OL,3,CHow is AI shaping the conflict in Iran?
OL,5,F"I think that there is just a general
OL,6,Ffeeling that artificial intelligence
OL,7,Fis something that we don't have full
OL,8,Fcontrol over. We just think we have
OL,9,Ffull control over.
OL,11,F"I think as long as that kind of idea
OL,12,Fcontinues to go on, of thinking of it
OL,13,Fas an alternative intelligence, the
OL,14,Ffear will be that AI is doing
OL,15,Fsomething to war that actually wasn't
OL,16,Fbeing done already."
OL,18,FFrom Westminster to Washington DC -
OL,19,Four political experts are across all
OL,20,Fthe latest key talking points. Listen
OL,21,Fto the latest episode below...
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G18/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
